{"name":"Aqua Delerium","type":"consumable","img":"modules/drakkenheim-adventure-module-for-pathfinder-2nd-edition/artwork/icons/items/AquaDelerium_Icon.webp","system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>This purple potion glows dimly with octarine light. It swirls and sparkles in its small stoppered bottle. When you drink this potion, you regain expended spell slots. Roll [[/r 1d6]] - you choose spell slots to regain that have a combined level that is equal to or less than the result. None of the slots can be higher than 5th level. For one hour after drinking aqua delerium, roll [[/r 1d20]] each time you cast a spell of 1st level or higher. On a 1, you trigger a random <strong>arcane anomaly</strong>.</p>\n<hr />\n<p style=\"text-align:left\">If you consume more than one dose of aqua delerium before finishing your next long rest, you take [[/r 1d12[negative]]]{1d12 negative damage} for each spell level regained, and your hit point maximum is reduced by an amount equal to the damage taken until the next time you rest. This damage canâ€™t be reduced or prevented in any way. When a creature who cannot cast spells using spell slots drinks aqua delerium, it takes [[/r 3d6[negative]]]{3d6 negative damage} and gains one level of @UUID[Compendium.world.dungeons-of-drakkenheim-campaign-effects.nhnDjKWBzz6OvZFx]{Contamination}.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Dungeons of Drakkenheim"},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.835,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2023-06-12T12:34:24.102-04:00","version":{"schema":0.812,"foundry":"10.291","system":"4.10.4"}}},"level":{"value":3},"traits":{"value":["arcane","consumable","magical","potion"],"rarity":"rare","otherTags":[]},"quantity":1,"baseItem":null,"hp":{"brokenThreshold":0,"value":0,"max":0},"hardness":0,"weight":{"value":"L"},"equippedBulk":{"value":""},"price":{"value":{}},"equipped":{"carryType":"worn","handsHeld":0},"stackGroup":null,"negateBulk":{"value":"0"},"containerId":null,"preciousMaterial":{"value":null},"preciousMaterial